messages.text: Hey! What are you doing?
I miss you. Call me ;)
I can't. I'm told my parent's I'm studying.
Why weren't you at school today?
Wasn't feeling well. :-(
I think I caught whatever it is that Lauren has.
She's always coughing without covering her mouth :-|
Nasty.
Lol.
Call me. You can just whisper so your parent's don't hear.
I seriously can't.
Plus I need to actually study or I'll fail chem.
I think I'm going to bed.
Will you tell me a bedtime story?
A bedtime story?
Yeah, like a fairytale about a princess and a prince and magic...
A lot of those are super dark.
Cinderella's stepsisters cut off their toes and heel before Cinderella got the slipper and it was filled with blood.
Eww.
It's true. Read it.
I don't want to read it.
Don't tell me a story like that. I want u to make it up. Tell me a happy one.
Umm okay...
I don't know what to say.
Start with "Once upon a time..."
Once upon a time there was a princess.
What was her name?
Lauren
Shut up!
J/k her name was Remi. Princess Remi.
That's better. :-D
Did she have a prince?
Are you going to let me tell this or not!
Sorry. Continue.
Princess Remi was beautiful but very lonely.
Why was she lonely?
I'm done.
No! Continue. I'm sorry. Keep going with the story.
She was beautiful and friendly and everyone loved her.
Aww.
But she was lonely because she lived at the highest tower of the castle. And she was sick.
Oh no! :-(
And no one in the kingdom knew how to cure her.
They searched all over the kingdom and still they could find nothing. The princess' health continued to fail.
She was dying.
I don't like this story. Start over. Tell a different story.
Don't worry this one has a happy ending.
Ok.
The kingdom did not know what to do and fell into despair.
Until one day a handsome knight on a white stallion rode into town.
Ohhhh.
And everyone rejoiced because they hoped he might be able to cure the princess.
The knight went to the castle to visit the princess.
And at first glance they instantly fell in love?
No.
Stop interrupting or I wont finish the story.
Sorry.
He climbed the tallest tower to the princess' room and peaked through her window.
And he saw that she was not sick at all. She was jus pretending.
The princess had fooled everyone, but not the knight. He knew that she was a faker and a liar and a cheat.
Michael what are you talking about?
Just follow the story. It gets good. I promise you'll like it.
Michael...
Shall I continue?
The princess climbed out her bed and looked out of the window.
Are you here? Are you watching me?
Princess Remi seemed afraid now.
She looked out of window.
Where are you?
But she did not see anyone.
What kind of story is this?
It's a fairytale.
The knight waited for the princess to leave her tower, and when she did he left a note on her dresser.
Remi?
Don't you want to know what the note said?
U r starting to freak me out.
Don't be freaked out. It's just a story.
Remi, don't you want to know what the note said?
Look on your dresser Remi.
You were in my room?!
Do you see it?
Yes.
What does it say? Tell me what it says.
"You weren't where you were supposed to be. I saw you but you didn't see me. "
What are you talking about?! Were you following me?
Michael?
Now alarmed the fair princess descended from her tower.
She ran all the way down the stairs. And at the bottom of the stairs she found a gift waiting for her.
Remi go down the stairs.
I don't want to. You're scarring me Michael.
Go down the stairs Remi...
Okay.
You there?
Yes.
What do you see?
It's a watch. It's broken. It's stuck at 9.
And what else do you see?
There is a note attached.
What does it say?
You already know what it says.
Tell me what it says!
"At the stroke of nine, a handsome knight you will find."
Why are you doing this to me? I didn't do anything I swear. I don't know who you think you saw...
You're a liar!
I wasn't with anyone! I don't know what any of this is about.
I saw you!
Saw what?! Where did you see me?!
Does it matter?
I want to know where you think you saw me?
At the bus stop around the corner from school where anyone could see you Remi.
I forgot to say that this princess was dumb.
You were laughing with him. And you held his hand. And you kissed him.
Who?
You know who! That gross slob.
Would the princess rather have a slob than a knight?!
Why are you doing this?
The beautiful princess began to cry because she it was true that she is a liar and a cheat and now everyone knows.
Please stop!
And she wept and wept and wept. And she asked for forgiveness.
I'm sorry Michael. Michael please....
But the knight was not convinced. He did not believe her apology.
He was angry and vowed to make the princess pay for her dishonestly.
What are you going to do?
Michael?
What time is it Remi?
What are you going to do?
For the fibber there is no cure. Answer the knock at the door.
Don't do this. Please just go home.
It's 9. Open the door Remi.
No.
Don't be afraid. It's just your handsome knight.
Just go away! I'm going to call the police.
There's no need for that Remi. I told you that this story ends happily. For the knight.
Open the door Remi.
I want you to tell me a bedtime story.
